description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen at the Queen Elizabeth Hospital Birmingham Chemotherapy Day Unit for a band 5 Staff Nurse The day unit provides a wide range of treatments for Oncology patients receiving chemotherapy and supportive therapies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit motivated skilled nurses to support our existing chemotherapy nursing team. Chemotherapy experience is preferable but not essential. All training is supported by chemotherapy trainers, a clinical educator, and the education department. As a band 5 staff nurse you will have the opportunity to develop both personally and professionally and have access to educational opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have acute care experience, excellent communication skills, and have the ability to work in a team then please apply for the available vacancy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Andrea Fernyhough on the following number: 0121 371 6213 or 07785347134 (andrea.fernyhough@uhb.nhs.uk.)&lt;/p&gt;
